android.car.hardware.property

类 CruiseControlType

  • java.lang.Object
    • android.car.hardware.property.CruiseControlType

  • public class CruiseControlType
extends java.lang.Object
    Used to enumerate the current type of VehiclePropertyIds.CRUISE_CONTROL_TYPE.

    This enum could be extended in future releases to include additional feature states.

    • 嵌套类概要

    • 字段概要

      字段 
      限定符和类型 字段和说明
      static int ADAPTIVE
      Adaptive cruise control is when a system in the vehicle automatically accelerates and decelerates to maintain a set speed and/or a set time gap from a vehicle ahead.
      static int OTHER
      This state is used as an alternative for any CruiseControlType value that is not defined in the platform.
      static int PREDICTIVE
      Predictive cruise control is a version of adaptive cruise control that also considers road topography, road curvature, speed limit and traffic signs, etc. to actively adjust braking, acceleration, gear shifting, etc. for the vehicle.
      static int STANDARD
      Standard cruise control is when a system in the vehicle automatically maintains a set speed without the driver having to keep their foot on the accelerator.

    • 字段详细资料

      • OTHER

        public static final int OTHER
        This state is used as an alternative for any CruiseControlType value that is not defined in the platform. Ideally, implementations of VehiclePropertyIds.CRUISE_CONTROL_TYPE should not use this state. The framework can use this field to remain backwards compatible if CruiseControlType is extended to include additional types.
        另请参阅:
        常量字段值

      • STANDARD

        public static final int STANDARD
        Standard cruise control is when a system in the vehicle automatically maintains a set speed without the driver having to keep their foot on the accelerator. This version of cruise control does not include automatic acceleration and deceleration to maintain a set time gap from a vehicle ahead.
        另请参阅:
        常量字段值

      • ADAPTIVE

        public static final int ADAPTIVE
        Adaptive cruise control is when a system in the vehicle automatically accelerates and decelerates to maintain a set speed and/or a set time gap from a vehicle ahead.
        另请参阅:
        常量字段值

      • PREDICTIVE

        public static final int PREDICTIVE
        Predictive cruise control is a version of adaptive cruise control that also considers road topography, road curvature, speed limit and traffic signs, etc. to actively adjust braking, acceleration, gear shifting, etc. for the vehicle. This feature is often used to optimize fuel consumption.
